Sibling defect to frankenredis-cikty / kwvqi / 0bxcy (replication-precondition family). Differential probe vs upstream Redis 7.2.4 replication.c::syncCommand:971-976:

  /* Refuse SYNC requests if we are a slave but the link with our master
   * is not ok... */
  if (server.masterhost && server.repl_state != REPL_STATE_CONNECTED) {
      addReplyError(c,'-NOMASTERLINK Can\'t SYNC while not connected with my master');
      return;
  }

When fr is itself a replica (Replica role) AND its master link isn't fully connected, upstream rejects incoming PSYNC/SYNC requests from chain-replicas — because serving stale data as a sync source would break the consistency invariant. Once the master link comes back up (state == 'connected'), chained replication is allowed again.

fr-runtime's handle_psync_command at crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs:11513-11587 has no such gate. A chain-replica client that connects during fr's reconnect window receives a FULLRESYNC reply pointing at fr's stale primary_offset, and the chain-replica sees a divergent history relative to the true master.

Concrete repro:
  > REPLICAOF master 6379       (fr enters Replica role with state='connect')
  (master link not yet established; state != 'connected')
  > PSYNC ? -1                  (sent by chain-replica connection)
  fr returns:  +FULLRESYNC <replid> <stale-offset>   (incorrectly serves)
  upstream:    (error) NOMASTERLINK Can't SYNC while not connected with my master

ReplicationRoleState::Replica carries a  static-str field that fr already uses elsewhere (e.g., role transitions). The 'connected' value indicates link-up; everything else (connect / connecting / receive_ping_reply / ...) means the link isn't ready.

Fix: in handle_psync_command, after the arity check and before any partial/full-sync decision, test:

  if let ReplicationRoleState::Replica { state, .. } =
      &self.server.replication_runtime_state.role
  {
      if *state != "connected" {
          return RespFrame::Error(
              "NOMASTERLINK Can't SYNC while not connected with my master".to_string(),
          );
      }
  }

Note the leading 'NOMASTERLINK' (no -ERR/-NOMASTERLINK prefix in fr; RespFrame::Error wraps with '-' on the wire, so the body string starts with the keyword directly — matches upstream's addReplyError('-NOMASTERLINK...') wire shape).

Acceptance: a chain-replica PSYNC against a Replica-state runtime with state='connect' returns the NOMASTERLINK error. The same call against state='connected' (chain-replication path) and against Master role both succeed. Existing PSYNC tests stay green; clippy clean.

